# Training Rules

## Loss
- Primary: nn.BCEWithLogitsLoss(reduction='mean') on raw logits vs float32 targets in [0,1]
- Smoothness: (Sigmoid(logits)[:,1:] - Sigmoid(logits)[:,:-1]).abs().mean()
- Length: nn.SmoothL1Loss()(log_pred_T, log_true_T)
- Total: bce_w * bce + smooth_w * smooth + length_w * length

## Data split (CRITICAL — no leakage)
- Split by CANONICAL ACTION NAME, not by clip
- canonical(id) = id with _clipN and trailing _N stripped, lowercased, underscores to spaces
- Group all clips of same canonical name -> assign entire group to one split
- Shuffle groups with seed=42, split 90/5/5
- Filter T < min_T BEFORE splitting

## Two-stage training
- Stage 1: head only, LR=3e-4, AdamW, weight_decay=1e-4
- Stage 2 (epoch >= unfreeze_after_epoch): apply LoRA, add lora param group at lora_lr=5e-6
- Save checkpoint BEFORE applying LoRA

## Teacher forcing (training only)
- Encode smplx_322 through VQ-VAE encoder -> motion tokens
- Use as decoder input instead of autoregressive generation
- Switch to autoregressive at inference

## Mixed precision and optimization
- torch.amp.autocast(device_type='cuda', dtype=torch.bfloat16) — no GradScaler for bf16
- clip_grad_norm_(head.parameters(), 1.0) every step
- zero_grad(set_to_none=True) every step
- Linear warmup + cosine decay

## Checkpointing
- Save: model state_dict, optimizer, epoch, best_val_loss
- Atomic: write .ckpt.tmp then rename to .ckpt
- Auto-resume: if checkpoint_dir/latest.ckpt exists at startup, load and continue
- Keep last N checkpoints (config.logging.keep_last_n_checkpoints)

## W&B logging
- Scalars every log_every_n_steps: train_loss, bce_loss, smooth_loss, length_loss, lr
- Full metrics every eval_every_n_epochs: MPJAE, per-muscle R2, bias, smoothness, length_mae
- Activation histograms every 10 epochs (check for sigmoid saturation)
- Sample table every 10 epochs: 8 val sequences with text + pred_T + true_T
